# Automation Loop Early-Exit on Zero-Work Pass

v1.1.0 covered early-exit/convergence wiring and summary/convergence consistency:
`run_loop` exits when every convergence phase reports zero work, `_summarize_loop`
must count the same `work_units` signal as the convergence predicate, `implement`
does not write work reports, and explicit issue sets that fully filter out should
warn while auto-discovery stays quiet.
